data$y <- as.factor(data$y)
box_data <- data %>%
  select(age, balance, day, duration, campaign, pdays, previous, y)
long_data <- pivot_longer(box_data, cols = -y, names_to = "variable", values_to = "value")

# Boxplots of Age, Balance, Day, Duration, Campaign, Pdays, Previous
boxplot(age ~ y, data = data, main = "Age by Subscription", col = "lightblue")

boxplot(balance ~ y, data = data, main = "Balance by Subscription", col = "lightgreen")

boxplot(day ~ y, data = data, main = "Day by Subscription", col = "lightpink")

boxplot(duration ~ y, data = data, main = "Duration by Subscription", col = "lightyellow")

boxplot(campaign ~ y, data = data, main = "Campaign by Subscription", col = "lightgray")

boxplot(pdays ~ y, data = data, main = "Pdays by Subscription", col = "lightcyan")

boxplot(previous ~ y, data = data, main = "Previous by Subscription", col = "lavender")

#Numerical Variables
num_data <- data %>%
  select(age, balance, day, duration, campaign, pdays, previous)
long_num <- pivot_longer(num_data, everything(), names_to = "variable", values_to = "value")

# Histogram 
ggplot(long_num, aes(x = value)) +
  geom_histogram(fill = "steelblue", bins = 30, color = "white") +
  facet_wrap(~variable, scales = "free", ncol = 3) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Histograms of Numerical Variables", x = "Value", y = "Count")

# Select categorical variables
cat_data <- data %>%
  select(job, marital, education, default, housing, loan, contact, month, poutcome, y)
long_cat <- pivot_longer(cat_data, everything(), names_to = "variable", values_to = "value")

# Bar plots
ggplot(long_cat, aes(x = value)) +
  geom_bar(fill = "steelblue", color = "black") +
  facet_wrap(~variable, scales = "free", ncol = 3) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Bar Graphs of Categorical Variables", x = "Category", y = "Count") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1))

#Lasso Regression
library(glmnet)
## Loading required package: Matrix
## 
## Attaching package: 'Matrix'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:tidyr':
## 
##     expand, pack, unpack
## Loaded glmnet 4.1-8
data$y <- ifelse(data$y == "yes", 1, 0)

# Create model matrix (drops intercept column automatically)
x <- model.matrix(y ~ age + job + marital + education + default + balance + housing + 
                    loan + contact + day + month + duration + campaign + pdays + 
                    previous + poutcome, 
                  data)[, -1]

# Response variable
y <- data$y

# Fit LASSO with cross-validation
cv_lasso <- cv.glmnet(x, y, alpha = 1, family = "binomial")

# Best lambda (penalty parameter)
best_lambda <- cv_lasso$lambda.min

# Plot cross-validation curve
plot(cv_lasso)

# Coefficients at optimal lambda
lasso_coef <- coef(cv_lasso, s = "lambda.min")
print(lasso_coef)
